The method returns an integer representing the earliest second starting from which the network becomes idle.
The network is considered idle if there is no network activity.
The network activity is determined by the pattern "pat".
The network activity follows the pattern "pat" until it becomes idle.
The network becomes idle when there are no more network activities according to the pattern "pat".
The network may become idle at any second after the initial state.
The network remains idle after it becomes idle.
